SABIE – The body of a 15-year-old was retrieved from a farm near the town on Monday. Ehlanzeni Diving Unit, Orru and SAPS retrieved the body of an unidentified man later yesterday afternoon.  He was discovered by Sappi workers at the bottom of a 15-metre cliff about 30 kilometres outside of White River. It is believed that he was pushed. Police said he is believed to be a man from Matsulu who was reported missing two months ago.  More information will be published as it becomes available.